This paper deals with joint vision and language tasks, specifically visual question answering, which falls under the intersection of computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CL and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a model that exploits biases in the dataset, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses the importance of word embeddings, which is a common topic in machine learning and natural language processing, making cs.LG a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval, as it aims to answer questions based on textual and visual information, making cs.IR a possible sub-category as well.
